@page "/denied"

@* Where the cookie handler's AccessDeniedPath lands a signed-in user who direct-loads a URL
   above their level. In-app navigations to such pages never get here — they're caught by
   Routes.razor's NotAuthorized branch, which shows the same message. Lives outside Pages/
   (like Login.razor) so the folder-wide [Authorize] doesn't gate it, though only signed-in
   users are ever redirected here. *@

<PageTitle>No access</PageTitle>

<div class="admin-page">
    <h1>No access</h1>
    <p>Your account doesn't have permission to open this page. Ask a manager if you think you should.</p>
    <a href="/">← Back to stations</a>
</div>
